    "text": "India is a South Asia country with a DB-type pension system centred on the Employees' Pension Scheme 1995 (EPS-95). The system includes 2 schemes: Employees' Pension Scheme 1995 (EPS-95), National Pension System (NPS) \u2013 Tier I. The normal retirement age is 58 for both men and women. Contributions total 8.3% of insurable earnings (0.0% employee, 8.3% employer).",
